017}}</ref>{{efn|name=Harding|Term began when President Harding died on August 2.}}<br />(Friday) || Private ||rowspan=2| {{sort|coolidgea|[[First inauguration of Calvin Coolidge]]}} || [[Coolidge Homestead]],<br />[[Plymouth Notch, Vermont|Plymouth Notch]], [[Vermont]] || {{sort|coolidge|[[John Calvin Coolidge, Sr.|John Calvin Coolidge]]}}<br />[[Notary public]]\n|-\n|{{dts|1923|08|21}}<ref name=prologuemag />{{efn|name=Harding}}<br />(Tuesday) || Private ||  [[Willard InterContinental Washington|Willard Hotel]]<br />Washington, D.C. || {{sort|hoehling|[[Adolph A. Hoehling, Jr.]]<br />Judge, [[U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia]]}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1925|03|04}}<br />(Wednesday) || Public || {{sort|coolidgeb|[[Second inauguration of Calvin Coolidge]]}} || East Portico,<br />U.S. Capitol || {{sort|tafta|[[William Howard Taft|William H. Taft]]<br />Chief Justice of the United States}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1929|03|04}}<br />(Monday) || Public || {{sort|hoover|[[Inauguration of Herbert Hoover]]}} || East Portico,<br />U.S. Capitol || {{sort|taftb|William H. Taft<br />Chief Justice}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1933|03|04}}<br />(Saturday) || Public || {{sort|rooseveltfa|[[First inauguration of Franklin D. Roosevelt]]}} || East Portico,<br />U.S. Capitol || {{sort|hughesa|[[Charles Evans Hughes|Charles E. Hughes]]<br />Chief Justice of the United States}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1937|01|20}}<br />(Wednesday) || Public || {{sort|rooseveltfb|[[Second inauguration of Franklin D. Roosevelt]]}} || East Portico,<br />U.S. Capitol || {{sort|hughesb|Charles E. Hughes<br />Chief Justice}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1941|01|20}}<br />(Monday) || Public || {{sort|rooseveltfc|[[Third inauguration of Franklin D. Roosevelt]]}} || East Portico,<br />U.S. Capitol || {{sort|hughesc|Charles E. Hughes<br />Chief Justice}}\n|-\n| {{dts|1945|01|20}}<br />(Saturday) || Public || {{sort|rooseveltfd|[[Fourth inauguration of Franklin D. Roosevelt]]}} || South Portico,<br />[[White House]] || {{sort|stonea|[[Harlan Fiske Stone|Harlan