s/r/5b5419b2-1db0-4bd7-b7b8-a16a3cc00654|title=Gloucestershire Rural Community Council|last=|first=|date=|publisher=National Archives|year=|isbn=|location=|language=English|access-date=24 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724132917/https://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/5b5419b2-1db0-4bd7-b7b8-a16a3cc00654|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live|ref={{harvid|National Archives|2019}}}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=D9Q_AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA254&lpg=PA254&dq=%22128,577%22+re-interments#v=onepage|title=Parliamentary Debates: House of Representatives|date=1920|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|ref={{harvid|Parliamentary Debates|1920}}|pages=|language=en|last1=|first1=}}\n\n=== Newspapers, gazettes & journals===\n\n* {{Cite news|url=|title=Solution for war dead|last=Byrne|first=Eugene|date=18 March 2014|work=The Post|access-date=|ref=harv}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=RDgnAAAAMAAJ&q=President+of+Executive+of+the+%22Parents'+National+Educational+Union%22+%22fabian+ware%22&dq=President+of+Executive+of+the+%22Parents'+National+Educational+Union%22+%22fabian+ware%22|title=Journal of Education|last=|first=|date=1939|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=|volume=71|location=|language=en|ref={{harvid|Journal of Education|1939}}}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Love|first=Gary|date=2014|title=The Periodical Press and the Intellectual Culture of Conservatism in Interwar Britain|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/historical-journal/article/periodical-press-and-the-intellectual-culture-of-conservatism-in-interwar-britain/147A806451D9E53E4B48952B28B631F5|journal=The Historical Journal|publisher=Cambridge University Press|volume=57|issue=4|pages=1027\u20131056|doi=10.1017/S0018246X14000429|url-access=subscription|via=|access-date=26 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906005301/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/historical-journal/article/periodical-press-and-the-intellectual-culture-of-conservat